com.foreach.across.modules.entity.support.properties

Class EntityIdProxyPropertyRegistrar

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.support.properties.EntityIdProxyPropertyRegistrar
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<EntityPropertyRegistryBuilder,EntityPropertyRegistryBuilder.PropertyDescriptorBuilder>

    public class EntityIdProxyPropertyRegistrar
extends Object
implements Function<EntityPropertyRegistryBuilder,EntityPropertyRegistryBuilder.PropertyDescriptorBuilder>
    Helper for registering an entity id proxy property: a new property of a specific entity type, which references another property which represents the entity id.

    Useful for mapping entities which are only referenced by id to their actual target instances (and back). The new property will inherit some configuration settings (like visibility) from the original property, and will have a default configuration that should work for both reading and updating the target property. This will also enable EntityQuery support for the new property.

    Can be used on EntityPropertyRegistryBuilder.property(Function), for example: 

    
 props -> props.property( propertyRegistrationHelper.entityIdProxy("author").entityType(Author.class).targetPropertyName("authorId") )
    The above example will create a property author of entity type Author, which will loads its value by id using the value of the authorId property. When setting a value on author it will automatically be translated to setting a value on authorId instead.
    Since:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
